 HAZYVIEW – Spes-Plan Security’s control room received an emergency signal from a guard at the Total filling station near Numbi Hotel in Hazyview at around 18:00 on Friday. An alleged armed robbery took place at the ATM inside the shop. It is understood that the robbers also attacked the cash registers inside the store.  Five suspects fled the scene. Saps and Spes-Plan Security followed in the direction of Sandrivier and found the one vehicle a kilometre before the Numbi turnoff on the R538 from Hazyview. A shootout ensued and a suspect was fatally wounded. Two suspects were injured and two fled.
It is believed that the vehicle had been involved in numerous armed robberies in the area. 